 the MIPS 24 micron survey, allowing one to obtain\nreliable source counts down to ~40 microJy. The extrapolation of the source\ncounts down to fainter fluxes suggests that our 24 micron sample is able to\nresolve ~62% of the cosmic background down to a flux level of 38 microJy.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 18 Nov 2005 15:38:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-11"}
